objects.name: IcedID Malware
objects.description:
Also known as Bokbot, IcedID is an information stealer and backdoor that first appeared as a banking Trojan in 2017 [1]. Since then, it has evolved. The criminal group behind IcedID also acts as an initial access broker for other criminal groups.

In an Active Directory (AD) environment, IcedID infections lead to network mapping, with criminals using tools like ADfind.exe, an AD enumeration utility [2]. Criminals use access from IcedID to collect information about AD users, systems, organizational units, subnets, groups, and trust objects.

In recent years, IcedID routinely has routinely led to Cobalt Strike and lateral movement within a targeted AD network. Cobalt strike is a known precursor to ransomware like Conti [3].

IcedID is distributed through different campaigns run by different threat actors, but the end result is the same. Regardless of the distribution channel, IcedID causes remote access, data exfiltration, and follow-up activity like Cobalt Strike and ransomware.

[1] https://securityintelligence.com/new-banking-trojan-icedid-discovered-by-ibm-x-force-research/
[2] https://thedfirreport.com/2021/06/20/from-word-to-lateral-movement-in-1-hour/
[3] https://thedfirreport.com/2022/04/04/stolen-images-campaign-ends-in-conti-ransomware/

objects.name: Polyglot File Delivers IcedID
objects.description:
Unit 42 recently observed a polyglot Microsoft Compiled HTML Help (CHM) file being employed in the infection process used by the information stealer IcedID. The technique involves executing the same CHM file twice in the infection process. The first execution exhibits benign activities, while the second execution stealthily carries out malicious behaviors. This particular attack chain delivered IcedID, also known as Bokbot, as the final payload. 
-------------------------------------------
@Unit42_Intel 2022-08-08

#IcedID (#Bokbot) infection led to #CobaltStrike. Password-protected zip file in email extracts ISO image to install #IcedID. Follow-on activity with #CobaltStrike. 

IOCs at https://github.com/pan-unit42/tweets/blob/master/2022-08-08-IOCs-for-IcedID-and-Cobalt-Strike.txt
